1.title: Cats and Dawgs Plus a Side of Eggs
1.plot: Two San Diego area high schools have been chosen to build a drag car in twelve weeks - El Camino and Ramona. Head judge, and six-time top fuel champ, Clay Millican, stops in to see the cars and meet the new teams.

1.title: Definitions
1.plot: Students of Tennessee high schools East Hickman and Fairview are selected to participate in a drag car building competition. Only on SPEED. Cars, automotive, drag race high, high school car shop, television, video.

2.title: Stripped
2.plot: East Hickman High strips their car down to a shell and Fairview High prepares their car to go to the chassis shop. Both schools struggle to find parts.

3.title: Daphne Blue
3.plot: Fairview High finds miscommunication with the chassis shop and is concerned they can't make the deadline. East Hickman High has a change of crew chiefs and decides what color to paint their car.

4.title: Haves and the Have Nots
4.plot: Fairview High falls farther behind as lack of parts and a finished chassis continue to plague their progress. East Hickman High moves full steam ahead and paints their car.

5.title: Zero to Hero
5.plot: Both schools hold car shows to raise money. Head judge, Charles Hendrickson, stops in to see both schools' progress. With both schools having losing football records, Fairview and East Hickman square off in a rivalry preview.

6.title: Third Time's a Charm
6.plot: East Hickman, dynos their car and takes it on its maiden voyage while Fairview sends their car to another shop in hopes of making the impending race day deadline. Six-time IHRA Top Fuel Champ Clay Millican visits both schools.

7.title: Race Day
7.plot: After reviewing both cars at Beech Bend Raceway, the judges struggle with their decision.

8.title: A New Hope
8.plot: With a new deadline and a renewed sense of purpose Fairview gets their troubled project on track. East Hickman continues to hone their race car.

9.title: The Winner Is ...
9.plot: Fairview's newly completed tube chassis Monza goes toe-to-toe with East Hickman's "Eagle One" in Bradenton, Florida.

imdb.plot outline: Drag Race High returns with its sophomore season as two highly contested SoCal rivals battle it out in shop class and on the track. There is pride and glory at stake this season as one school will win the other's car and bragging rights for a year. Each school is working towards making sure it has the best mechanics, a superior body shop, a detail-oriented team and someone paying attention to the clock. One school will win it all; the other may be looking up the meaning of defeat. Only on SPEED.
